SUMMARY:LC Spring 2026 MainStage Production: “When We Slept in Trees”
DESCRIPTION:When We Slept in Trees is a devised dance/theatre piece led by faculty members Rebecca Lingafelter (director) and Tiffany Mills (movement director)\, along with designers Jenny Ampersand (costume) and Miranda Hardy (set and lights)\, this piece is devised by the company.\n\nThe source material is rooted in the relationship between human beings and the natural world and draws from numerous sources including poetry\, movement\, music\, storytelling and visual art.\n\nMarch 6-8 at 7:30pm\nMarch 8 at 2pm\nMarch 12-14 at 7:30pm\n\nCost: $5\, 10\, 15\nEditor’s note: This event is a community submission.
URL:https://pdxparent.com/event-single/lc-spring-2026-mainstage-production-when-we-slept-in-trees/2026-03-12/
LOCATION:Lewis and Clark College\, 615 S Palatine Hill Rd\, Portland\, OR\, 97219\, United States
CATEGORIES:Dance,Kids Calendar,Music,Theater
